Then, it converts the cleaned input to lowercase and reverses it using the `reverse` method of the `StringBuilder` class.

Next, it creates a `HashSet` called `uniqueCharacters` to store the unique characters. It iterates through the reversed string and adds each character to the set. The set automatically removes duplicates.

Finally, it builds the final string by iterating through the unique characters in the set and appends them to a new `StringBuilder` called `result`. The `result` is then converted to a string using the `toString` method and returned.

